    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make all A-level courses modular based examinations",
        "additional_details": "if the exams were structured in a modular way, focus would be put on a students ability to engage with questions, focusing therefore on continuous progress throughout the two year period rather than simply remembering content for two years which is both unrealistic and flawed.",
        "background": "A-Levels are wrongly designed to benefit students who have greater capacity for memory. Therefore making the exams a test of memory rather than a students capability to answer comprehensive questions. Within the sixth form environment students experience unprecedented stress due to the examinations",
